<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4648] Bytes.toBigDecimal() doesn&apos;t use offset</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4648</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Bytes.toBigDecimal(byte[], offset, len) method does not use the offset, thus you will get an incorrect result for the BigDecimal unless the BigDecimal&apos;s bytes are at the beginning of the byte array.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Java 1.6.0_26, Mac OS X 10.7 and CentOS 6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12528411">HBASE-4648</key>
            <summary>Bytes.toBigDecimal() doesn&apos;t use offset</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
